<h3>Hegra Fort</h3></br>

<p>At a distance of less than 22 km from Al-Ula, the "Hijra" area is located 
in the middle of the desert and mountain canyons, which UNESCO considered a
 world heritage site, witnessing the civilization of the region during the Nabataean period
 The history of the area dates back to the middle of the first century BC. 
 It tells the story of the ancient Nabataean civilization, and suggests to the visitor 
 that that civilization is still present before his eyes. Hijra is located 
 south of the Jordanian city of Petra</p>
 <p>This archaeological wonder that previously formed the 
 trade route between the Arabian Peninsula 
 and the cities of the Mediterranean and Asia,</p></br>
